headline: Should Health Canada’s Approval of Abbott (ABT) Dissolvable Stent Drive a Rethink for Investors?
summary: Abbott Laboratories recently received Health Canada approval for the Esprit BTK Everolimus Eluting Resorbable Scaffold System, a first-of-its-kind dissolvable stent designed to treat chronic limb threatening ischemia below the knee using a minimally invasive approach. This innovative device not only keeps arteries open and supports vessel healing, but also significantly reduces the need for repeat procedures in a condition with high rates of amputation and mortality.
